## Global behavior (all projects) — User Rules

This file applies **this repo only** when `alwaysApply: true` is loaded from `.cursor/rules/`.

To get the **same behavior in every workspace**:

1. Open **Cursor Settings** → **Rules for AI** → **User Rules** (global).
2. Copy everything **from** `# Clarify first, then implement` **through** `# This repo` above (omit the “This repo” section if you want rules to stay generic, or keep a one-line “respect project AGENTS.md / .cursor/rules” note).
3. Save. Reload the window if rules do not pick up immediately.

Path reference (Windows): settings are in the Cursor app; User Rules are edited in the **Rules for AI** UI, not only in `settings.json`.
